The Senate Energy Committee on Wednesday wrote to Auditor General Edward Ouko, asking him to carry out a special audit of the Mombasa-Nairobi pipeline.The decision by the committee chaired by Baringo Senator Gideon Moi has been informed by failure of the main contractor, Zakhem International Constructions Ltd, to honour invites and summons issued by the team.&ldquo;Attempts to meet the main the contractor have proved unsuccessful. However, meetings with Kenya Pipeline Company and the subcontractors working on the pipeline indicate the project was near completion with many contractors having completed their work,&rdquo; the team says in a letter dated June 13.In particular, the committee wants the auditor to establish if there was value for money on the pipeline.